title: PPPP’s  Azra Fazal Pechuho wins PS- 36 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) Azra Fazal Pechuho has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-36, Shaheed Banazirabad- I by securing 75866 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Mir Bhawal Khan Rind of Independent, who bagged votes 16228.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 44.69 %.
